So, without further ado, let’s get started.

00:01:19.682 --> 00:01:24.302
There is a saying that the sun never set on the British Empire.

00:01:25.652 --> 00:01:32.762
At its zenith, at its greatest point, it stretched over huge swathes of the world,

00:01:33.092 --> 00:01:41.342
covering 35 million kilometres squared, with 412 million people living under its rule.

00:01:42.352 --> 00:01:47.362
It propelled English to be the world’s lingua franca, the common language,

